# ── Copy to `.env` and fill secrets (never commit `.env`).
# ── On Vercel: Settings → Environment Variables (never upload `.env`).
# ⚠ Rotate keys/passwords if they were pasted in chat or leaked.
#
# ── Minimum set (5 variables on Vercel) ──
# Admin JWT is signed with SHA-256(SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY) when JWT_SECRET is unset.
# `lib/supabase.js` uses SUPABASE_URL + SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY (same as createClient in your script).
# Express SQL (login, CRM, stats) still uses `pg` + DATABASE_URL — PostgREST cannot replace raw SQL.

OPENAI_API_KEY=

SUPABASE_URL=https://mtsakeogxsrmpbtktndq.supabase.co
# Anon key is for browser Supabase clients; optional on this Node server unless you add REST-only features.
SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=paste_anon_jwt_here
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=paste_service_role_jwt_here

# Postgres (same DB admin + chatbot use via `pg`). Password: URL-encode in URI (e.g. ! → %21)
# Direct `db.*.supabase.co:5432` is auto-rewritten to the Transaction pooler (IPv4) unless SUPABASE_AUTO_POOLER=false.
# If you get DB errors, set region (and optional prefix) from Supabase → Connect — host is often aws-1-REGION or aws-0-REGION:
# SUPABASE_POOLER_REGION=ap-northeast-1
# SUPABASE_POOLER_AWS_PREFIX=aws-1
# Or paste the full Transaction pooler URI and set SUPABASE_AUTO_POOLER=false.
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://postgres:YOUR_DB_PASSWORD_HERE@db.mtsakeogxsrmpbtktndq.supabase.co:5432/postgres

# ── Optional overrides ──
# JWT_SECRET=only-if-you-want-a-fixed-admin-token-key-instead-of-deriving-from-service-role
# API_DEBUG=1
# DATABASE_IPV4_FIRST=true

# Smoke tests: npm run verify-api [baseUrl] — ADMIN_TEST_EMAIL + ADMIN_TEST_PASSWORD for full login check

# First tables: npm run db:apply (or paste schema.sql in Supabase SQL editor)
# First admin: npm run seed-admin with ADMIN_EMAIL + ADMIN_PASSWORD in .env (CLI only)

# Optional CORS whitelist (server.js uses open CORS by default)
# ALLOWED_ORIGINS=https://your-chat.vercel.app

# Supabase TLS: do not set DATABASE_SSL=false against Supabase.
